Shailagh Murray has been announced as the new Communications Director for Vice President Biden, starting next month. She will be replacing Jay Carney, who has been appointed as the White House Press Secretary. Murray is a veteran journalist, previously working at the Washington Post. Vice President Biden praised her experience and knowledge on a range of issues, stating that her leadership and counsel will be invaluable. Murray has covered topics such as fiscal policy, health care reform, and national security, and has also reported on several elections. She has previously worked for the Wall Street Journal in both Washington, DC, and international locations. Murray will be joining a communications team that includes Press Secretary Elizabeth Alexander, Deputy Press Secretary Amy Dudley, and Assistant Press Secretary Liz Allen.